               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431211-name-299" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431211-name-299" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431211-name-299" type="surname" value="DERBY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431211-name-299" type="given" value="GEORGE JAMES"></interp>GEORGE JAMES DERBY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a schoolmaster, and live in Stepney-square. The prisoner was my servant—I found a man concealed in the out-home on the 4th of Dec., and sent the prisoner away the same night, and on searching, a shift and some calico were missed—next morning she came for her box—I accused her of taking these things, which she denied—the calico was found in her box—the said, "I confess that I have taken them," and produced the duplicate of the shift, which was in the mattress of her bed—it bad been pawned for 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> You promised me pardon, and I confessed. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> She was given to understand that she would be let off, but it was at her mother's re<lb></lb>quest that I prosecuted—she was without a home or money, and begged I would prosecute her, that some means might be found of providing for her.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431211-name-300" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431211-name-300" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
